This paper is about the development of self-adaptive software using a model-driven engineering approach. It focuses on the interplay between runtime models and adaptation activities, which are key concerns in software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also presents an executable modeling language for runtime megamodels, which involves the use of domain-specific modeling languages and runtime interpreters. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development), cs.PL (Programming Languages), or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper deals with self-adaptation, which is a topic of interest in the field of artificial intelligence. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
